@endpoint GET /v20180820/configuration/publicAccessBlock
@desc This operation is not supported by directory buckets.  Retrieves the PublicAccessBlock configuration for an Amazon Web Services account. For more information, see  Using Amazon S3 block public access. Related actions include:    DeletePublicAccessBlock     PutPublicAccessBlock
@required {x-amz-account-id: str}
@returns(200) {PublicAccessBlockConfiguration: PublicAccessBlockConfiguration?{BlockPublicAcls: bool?, IgnorePublicAcls: bool?, BlockPublicPolicy: bool?, RestrictPublicBuckets: bool?}}

